Interface IMsgAdpt<ADataPacket>

  • Type Parameters:
    ADataPacket - 

    public interface IMsgAdpt<ADataPacket>
    An interface that represents all adapter that sends message to chatRoom server. 1.
    Author:
    ChatApp Design Group E

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int ID
      ID ILocalMsgAdpt Since there are two types Adapter, system and chatroom.
      static IMsgAdpt<?> NULL_ADAPTER
      Null adapter object that only prints the given string to the standard err output.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String accept(ADataPacket datapacket)
      Send a message to the chatroom(Server) and return one of the three string response, Success, Failure, or Unknown.

    • Field Detail

      • ID

        static final int ID
        ID ILocalMsgAdpt Since there are two types Adapter, system and chatroom. The two types of Adapter will be sent to same port so require a ID to figure which adapter this is. Chatroom Adapter
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • NULL_ADAPTER

        static final IMsgAdpt<?> NULL_ADAPTER
        Null adapter object that only prints the given string to the standard err output. sendMSG will fail for Null_ADapter case.

    • Method Detail

      • accept

        java.lang.String accept(ADataPacket datapacket)
        Send a message to the chatroom(Server) and return one of the three string response, Success, Failure, or Unknown.
        Parameters:
        msg - String of msg sent to chatroom server.
        Returns:
        String of msg status. This status include 3 Success: message was received and processed properly Failure: message was not received. (no response from recipient) Unknown: message was received, but could not be processed
